---
source: src/tests.rs
expression: render_command_help(&refs)
---
Scroll the page or an element

Usage: bl scroll [OPTIONS] [direction] [COMMAND]

Commands:
  into-view  Scroll an element into view
  help       Print this message or the help of the given subcommand(s)

Arguments:
  [direction]  Scroll direction: up or down (default down)

Options:
      --amount <amount>      Number of scroll increments [default: 3]
  -v, --verbose              Enable debug logging
      --selector <selector>  CSS selector for element to scroll to [default: ""]
      --headless             Hide browser window (visible by default)
      --json                 Output as JSON
  -h, --help                 Print help

Examples:
  bl scroll
  # Scroll down by default

  bl scroll up
  # Scroll up

  bl scroll down --amount 5
  # Scroll down 5 increments

  bl scroll down --selector "div.content"
  # Scroll within a specific element
